trans-unit.source: Amaroq is named after an Inuit legend of a giant wolf, which is fitting for a companion to our friend the mastodon. May we all howl across the federated space! Amaroq is built and maintained by a love of the Mastodon idea, which sorely has needed a mobile outlet for our iOS friends. Got a suggestion, found a bug, or just want to voice some support? You can reach us at amarok.feedback@gmail.com. Or hit up the dev, @eurasierboy on the mastodon.social instance. Happy tooting!
trans-unit.target: El nombre de Amaroq proviene de una leyenda esquimal sobre un lobo gigante, el cual es un compañero apropiado para nuestro amigo el mastodonte. ¡Todos aullaremos a traves del espacio federado! Amaroq esta desarrollado y mantenido mediante el amor del movimiento Mastodon, que necesitaba apoyo para nuestros amigos de iOS. ¿Tienes alguna sugerencia, encontraste un error o solo quieres soporte? Puees contactaros en amarok.feedback@gmail.com. O contacta con el desarrollador @eurasierboy en la instancia mastodon.social. ¡Feliz tooting!

trans-unit.id: Amaroq is named after an Inuit legend of a giant wolf, which is fitting as a companion to our friend the mastodon. May we all howl across the fediverse!\n\nAmaroq is built and maintained by a love of the Mastodon idea, which sorely has needed a mobile outlet for our iOS friends. Got a suggestion, found a bug, or just want to voice some support? You can reach us at amaroq.feedback@gmail.com. Or hit up the dev, @eurasierboy on the mastodon.social instance. Happy tooting!
